               <floruit>He was a saintly figure from <placeName ref="LOC3549Gojjam">Goǧǧām</placeName>, a contemporary of <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe </roleName>
                  <persName ref="PRS10375Yohanne">Yoḥannǝs I</persName> and  <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName>
                  <persName ref="PRS5616IyasuI">ʾIyāsu I</persName>. Towards the end of his life, <persName ref="PRS10618ZaraB">Zarʾa Buruk</persName> appears to have been involved in the 
                  Christological controversies of his time. As a result of his disagreeing with <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe </roleName>
                  <persName ref="PRS5616IyasuI">ʾIyāsu I</persName>,  he was imprisoned for five years. 
                  His centre  of veneration is the church dedicated to him, St Michael at <placeName ref="LOC3403Gelgal">Gǝš ʾAbbāy</placeName>. 
